  "text": "Mammary tissue specimens were obtained from breast cancer patients undergoing surgery. Pure populations of epithelial cells were obtained as described previously [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The epithelial origin of the cultures was confirmed by immunofluorescence with an antiPan cytokeratin antibody (Sigma-Aldrich). Second-passage cells, practically free of nonepithelial cells, were used for all described experiments (Fig. S1  B) . MG132 was used at 10 M. 1 M DFP-AA (compound E; Calbiochem) was added in fresh medium every 24 h for 10 d. Mock-treated controls were exposed to equivalent concentrations of carrier (0.05% dimethyl sulfoxide).",
